## 0.6 Notion AI — Four Operational Modes

`Source: Official | Last verified: Mar 4, 2026 | Confidence: High`

### AI Autofill
**What it reads:** Page body content only. Cannot reference text in file attachments, URL properties, or linked database entries.
**Property types it can populate:** Text properties (Summary, Key Info, Translate, Custom prompt) · Select and Multi-select (AI category assignment; supports "Auto-update on page edits")
**The constraint that governs everything:** Empty or thin page body = empty or hallucinated output. No exceptions. Design page body standards before configuring Autofill.

### Q&A
**Searches:** Page titles, body content, and connected apps (Slack, Google Drive, GitHub — Enterprise Search). Respects all workspace permissions.
**Does well:** Finding pages, surfacing information from rich body content, answering questions that exist somewhere in the workspace.
**Fails reliably:** Structured database queries, counting records, aggregating values, precise filtering. Q&A is a content retrieval system, not a database query engine.
**What improves results:** Recently updated pages, rich body content, descriptive and specific page titles.

### Research Mode
Blends workspace knowledge with web research. Treat outputs as draft material. Ground anything critical against primary sources. Availability varies by plan and rollout.

### AI Meeting Notes
Transcription + structured summaries + action items. Notion 3.1: dedicated Meetings tab in sidebar. Summaries link each takeaway to the exact transcript moment. Full mobile parity (Notion 3.2).

