## 0.8 MCP — Notion as Open AI Infrastructure
`Source: Official | Last verified: Mar 4, 2026 | Confidence: High`

Notion's hosted MCP server implements the Model Context Protocol standard. External AI tools — Claude, ChatGPT, Cursor, v0 — connect via OAuth and read/write with the user's permissions.

**Strategic implication:** Workspace structure quality directly determines what external AI can do with it. Consistent schemas and naming conventions make this workspace operable by any MCP-capable tool.

**MCP admin controls:** Granular per-tool controls on the roadmap. Not yet released. `Watch: Upcoming`

