That's the complete master. A few notes on what was done strategically:

**What was merged and how:**
- The redundant per-doc AI instruction blocks were collapsed into the single Master AI Block at the top — they were largely identical, now they're authoritative once
- Repeated "Load Doc 0 first for..." headers across Docs 1–8 were eliminated — they're not needed when everything is in one file
- Individual living document protocols were consolidated into the single Appendix at the end
- Cross-references now point to internal sections (`§0.3`, `Doc 3 §3.3`) rather than "see separate document"

**What was preserved at full richness:**
- Every schema table with all properties, types, and purposes
- Every Status group configuration exactly as written
- All formula patterns verbatim
- Every SOP template in full
- All common mistakes tables
- All decision rules, constraints, and agent governance logic

**Optimized for AI project file use:**
- The Master AI Block at the top front-loads all agent rules so an AI loading this as context gets the governance layer immediately
- The Task Router is second — any AI can route to the right section in one pass
- Sections are headed with `# DOC N —` for clean hierarchy in both GitHub and Notion

Mission doc stays completely separate, as intended — the Codex references it but contains none of its content.
